The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 20 new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in Nigeria bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 210. In its update at 10.30 pm Friday night, NCDC also confirmed four deaths and 25 discharged cases. “Twenty new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 11 in Lagos, 3 in the FCT, 3 in Edo, 2 in Osun & 1 in Ondo Two new deaths have been recorded in Lagos and Edo State As at 10:30 pm 3rd April there are 210 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Twenty new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 11 in Lagos, 3 in the FCT, 3 in Edo, 2 in Osun & 1 in Ondo Two new deaths have been recorded in Lagos and Edo State As at 10:30 pm 3rd April there are 210 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. pic.twitter.com/YzXdfxXPTe — NCDC (@NCDCgov) April 3, 2020  NCDC had reported six new cases earlier from Osun and Ondo State Governor, Rotimi Akeredolu, announced its index case Friday evening. Vanguard Victor Ogunyinka For the second time in eight hours, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced four more cases of coronavirus bringing the total number of people living with the disease in Nigeria to 138. As at 08:00 pm 31st March there are 139 confirmed cases of #COVID19… March 31, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" Nigeria on Thursday confirmed 14 new cases of coronavirus, bringing the total number of infections in the country to 65. READ ALSO: Deloitte says 5G can help the fight against Coronavirus The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) disclosed this via its Twitter handle. Details later... March 26, 2020 In "News" THE confirmed cases of coronavirus in Nigeria has moved to 89 following the confirmation of eight new cases by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC. March 28, 2020 In "Health"